---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Atlas. | hideaway."
  description="Atlas turns scattered evidence into a usable map — so you stop building solutions to problems you can't quite see."
>
  <div class="solution-page">

    <div class="solution-header">
      <div class="solution-header-inner">
        <div class="solution-tag">Made by Laura</div>
        <h1>Atlas.</h1>
        <p class="solution-strapline">
          Turn scattered evidence into a usable map.
        </p>
        <div class="demo-cta">
          <a href="https://atlas-demo-1111.netlify.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-demo">Try the demo →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="solution-body">

      <section class="solution-section">
        <h2>The problem it solves</h2>
        <p>
          Organisations commission research. Consultations produce hundreds of responses. Reports
          pile up. And then — nothing changes, because nobody can see across all of it at once.
        </p>
        <p>
          The insight exists in the data. The problem is synthesis. By the time someone has read
          fifty documents and tried to find the patterns, the energy to act on them has usually gone.
          So problems stay invisible, and solutions get built for the wrong things.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="solution-section">
        <h2>What Atlas does</h2>
        <p>
          Atlas takes a collection of documents — consultation responses, research reports, policy
          papers, interview transcripts — and extracts insights, not summaries. It finds what
          the data means, not just what it says.
        </p>
        <p>
          Then it synthesises across documents to surface the patterns: where concerns cluster,
          where there's unexpected agreement, where the gaps are. The result is a map you can
          actually use — a starting point for decisions rather than a pile of paper to get through.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="solution-highlight">
        <blockquote>
          "We had 300 consultation responses. Atlas found the three things everyone kept saying
          that nobody had noticed yet."
        </blockquote>
        <cite>— Atlas pilot user, public sector consultation</cite>
      </div>

      <section class="solution-section">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>
          The pipeline has two stages. First, individual documents are processed through an
          extraction prompt that pulls out insights — specific, significant observations, with
          their source location attached. Not paraphrase. Not summary. What the document actually
          means.
        </p>
        <p>
          Second, the extracted insights from all documents are synthesised together. Atlas finds
          the repeating patterns, the contradictions, the things that appear once but matter
          disproportionately.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result is a structured output you can present, share, or use to brief a team in
          minutes instead of months.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="solution-section">
        <h2>Where it fits</h2>
        <p>
          Atlas is most useful wherever evidence is scattered across many documents and decisions
          need to be made from it — public consultations, user research synthesis, competitive
          analysis, policy review, due diligence.
        </p>
        <p>
          If your work involves making sense of large volumes of text before you can act, Atlas
          is built for you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="solution-cta">
        <h3>Interested in Atlas?</h3>
        <p>
          If you're working on evidence synthesis, research infrastructure, or have a specific
          use case in mind, get in touch.
        </p>
        <a href="/subscribe" class="btn-primary">Stay in the loop</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .solution-page {
    padding-top: 5rem;
  }

  .solution-header {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 5rem 3rem 4rem;
  }

  .solution-header-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .solution-tag {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--sage);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .solution-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #E8F547;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .solution-strapline {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .demo-cta {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .btn-demo {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #E8F547;
    color: var(--navy);
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.6rem;
    border-radius: 7px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-demo:hover {
    background: #d4e03a;
  }

  .solution-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 3rem 6rem;
  }

  .solution-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .solution-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .solution-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  .solution-highlight {
    background: var(--stone);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }

  .solution-highlight blockquote {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .solution-highlight cite {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #6b6254;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .solution-cta {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .solution-cta h3 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .solution-cta p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .solution-header {
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }

    .solution-body {
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    .solution-highlight {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
